x4freetext: Data for Np-237 measured by gamma-spectroscopy .
Capture gamma-ray detector consists of two
halves, each containing 8 optically separated BGO
crystals 1700 mm in length which form a cylindrical
scintillation layer having internal and external
diameters 110 and 210 mm respectively. Total volume
electron current 35 micro-A for 0.3 eV - 1 keV
average electron current 70 micro-A for 0.02 eV -
0.7 MeV. Slow neutrons produced by moderating of fast
neutrons in 10 cm thick water moderator
directed to 135 degree relative to flight path
